The paper discusses the conversion of Library of Congress Subject Headings (LCSH) to Simple Knowledge Organization System (SKOS) RDF, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL) research. The paper also highlights the strengths of SKOS vocabulary, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of other semantic web vocabularies such as Dublin Core, which is relevant to database (DB) research.
